          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sn01q4f/canvas/p2/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sn01q4f/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>And above all, in the name of conscience, you know<lb/> me, and all what it was\n                spoken about me, and why<lb/> have you chosen me to be one of your <add>בית\n                    דין</add> to make<lb/> the <add>גיורת</add>, why have you given me\n                    <add>קבלה</add>? Why have you<lb/>\n                <sic>deffended</sic> me against the man who spoke ill, of the<lb/>\n                <persName>Rev Mr. Rosenfield</persName>, of yourself and of me?\n                <sic>indeed</sic><lb/> sir, I see that my opinion of you from the very<lb/> first\n                time I knew you was true, I kept you for an<lb/>\n                <add>איש משוגע</add>, a <add>הפכפך</add>. It is indeed true the saying of the<lb/>\n                <add>גר\"א</add>—which in the name of <add>רבי מאיר</add> says he always<lb/>\n                considered a man by his name, and so I consider<lb/> you, it is not for nothing that\n                your name is vice,<lb/> but because you are the foundation of all viciousness<lb/>\n                since you came to this country the true faith found<lb/> its end, you trod true\n                religion under foot, you made<lb/>\n                <placeName>Israel</placeName>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">light</hi>\n                <sic>istaed</sic> of Israelite, in short sir you<lb/> are the man who can do good to\n                none, and even to<lb/> yourself without injuring another. Now sir, I will tell<lb/>\n                you what you are if none told you yet, you are no Talmudist at<lb/> all and your\n                Philosophy indeed while a child I knew it.<lb/> You can only fool ignorant man, but\n                among learned<lb/> what do you know? nothing—know therefore that it is<lb/> this\n                only time I write to answer you, and from now you can<lb/> write whatever you\n                please, no answer will be given to you<lb/> and this time I answer you only that you\n                should not say<lb/> that you silenced me, and to show you that your slandering<lb/>\n                can do me no harm Please God, you have great <add>חוצפה</add><lb/> because you are\n                sure of being engaged for life, and I am sure<lb/> in the help of the true living\n                God of <placeName>Israel</placeName>. <persName role=\"author\">E.\n                Marcuson</persName>.</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3sn01q4f/canvas/p2"
                }
